# FamilyManager REST examples
# Use with VS Code REST Client extension.
# Ensure the API is running on http://localhost:4000.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:4000/api/v1
@rootUrl = http://localhost:4000
@json = application/json

### Health check
GET {{rootUrl}}/health

### Register a new family (optional flow)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: {{json}}

{
  "email": "new.parent@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "familyName": "Example Family",
  "firstName": "Pat",
  "lastName": "Parent"
}

### Login with seeded parent user
# Default seeded password is "password" unless DEV_PARENT_PASSWORD was set.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{json}}

{
  "email": "anderson.parent@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Get current user (requires auth cookie from login)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me

### List event categories
GET {{baseUrl}}/event-categories

### List events for current family
GET {{baseUrl}}/events

### Create a new event
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Content-Type: {{json}}

{
  "title": "Sample event from REST client",
  "description": "Created via api.http",
  "startTime": "2026-04-14T18:00:00.000Z",
  "endTime": "2026-04-14T19:00:00.000Z",
  "categoryId": 1
}

### List family members
GET {{baseUrl}}/family-members

### Run reminder scheduler for current family (requires parent auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/notifications/reminders/run

### List current user's notifications
GET {{baseUrl}}/notifications
